'''Devaramane''' is a village in [[Mudigere]] Taluk, [[Chikkamagaluru]] district in the state of [[Karnataka]], [[India]]. The village is renowned for its Kalabhairaveshwara temple.

==Transport==
By Road: Regular buses ply from [[Bengaluru]] (259&nbsp;km), [[Chikkamagaluru]] (30 &nbsp;km), [[Hassan, Karnataka|Hassan]] (62&nbsp;km), [[Mangaluru]] (124&nbsp;km), [[Mysuru]](149&nbsp;km) to [[Mudigere]].
Nearest Railway: [[Hassan, Karnataka|Hassan]] (about 32&nbsp;km from [[Mudigere]]) Banavara and Arasikere are also near [[Mudigere]].
Nearest Airport: BIAL, Bengaluru about 259&nbsp;km from [[Mudigere]].

==Agriculture and commerce==
The primary mode of employment in the Devaramane region is agriculture. Crops grown include coffee, rice, finger millet, pepper, cardamom with paddy being dominant.

==Geography==
Belur is located at {{coord|13.061586|N|75.538752|E|}}.

